SLS camera configuration procedure.  Except for camserver itself, all
routines are in the hardware-specific directory, e.g. sls42.

camserver invokes cam_config_initialize() in cam_config.c
  1) read the system-wide confuration file, e.g. /usr/local/etc/camrc
  2) read the user's resource file, ~/.camrc
  3) read the project-specific camrc in the startup directory of camserver
     A) invoke camera_read_setup() in interface.c to read the camera
	    definition file, .../cam_data/camera.def
		  i) invoke read_camera_setup() in cam_tbl.c to configure the
		     the detector-specific software and hardware
			 a) invoke read_detecor_info() in signals.c to configure the
			    pattern generator software

  4) set up the cam_stat file system

camserver invokes camera_initialize() in interface.c.

camserver executes the cam_startup_file specified in camrc (default.set)
